                <note rend="inline" type="source">651.113/109a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France (<persName type="to">Edge</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-17T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 17, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>327. The copper interests are anxious to obtain relief from the discrimination in
                    favor of Belgium. Has there been any recent progress in this matter?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
